    • Constructor Detail

      • Client

        public Client(String str)
        Client object constructor. Creates a Client object based on a single line from a rcon "status" command. Parses out the guid, name, and client id.
        Parameters:
        str - The string will be a single line from a rcon status command. Example line: 9 70 309 aaaa1234567890bbbbbbcccccccddddd 77solor^7 0 75.35.141.4:9704

      • Client

        public Client(String id,
              String s,
              String n,
              String eN,
              String g)
        Client object constructor This constructor is for when the variables have already been parsed from a rcon reply. Use case ex creating a deep copy
        Parameters:
        id - will be the cid
        s - will be the score
        n - will be the name
        eN - becomes the exactName
        g - becomes the guid

      • checkGuid

        private void checkGuid()
        checkGuid() will check guid for any irregularities. prevents malfromed guids. If a malformed guid is found, calls the kickClient() method to invoke a rcon kick command. Guid spoofing is a common problem. This method will help combat some of it by detecting and kicking malformed guids
